Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Thursday confirmed 35 new coronavirus cases in the country. “Thirty-five new cases of #COVID19 have been reported as follows: 19 in Lagos, nine in FCT, five in Kano and two in Oyo,” NCDC tweeted. “As of 10:20 pm on the 16th of April, there are 442 confirmed cases of #COVID-19 reported in Nigeria. 152 have been discharged with 13 deaths.” Details later… To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .